Make a graph object of the tree by two ways; using the edge list and the adjacency matrix.

0619 Assignment

Make an adjacency matrix for n vertices that have k separated components, by manipulating the rectangular blocks of “zero-throughout”.

n <- 40
k <- 10
m <- n/k
emat <- matrix(0,n,n)
e.list <- matrix(sample(1:n,n),k,m)
e.list
##       [,1] [,2] [,3] [,4]
##  [1,]    4   26   25   10
##  [2,]   16   31    6   40
##  [3,]   17   27   23   18
##  [4,]   32    7   33   15
##  [5,]   21   37    1   35
##  [6,]    8   19   39   12
##  [7,]   29   36   28   22
##  [8,]   14    9    5   30
##  [9,]    2   13   38   34
## [10,]   11    3   20   24
for(i in 1:k){
  m.list <- e.list[i,]
  for(j in 1:m){
    for(h in 1:m){
      jj <- m.list[j]
      hh <- m.list[h]
      emat[jj,hh] <- 1
    }
  }
}
diag(emat) <- 0
g4 <- graph_from_adjacency_matrix(emat,mode="undirected")
plot(g4)
